'''Dharmottara''' (Tibetan: ''chos mchog'') was an 8th-century Buddhist author of several important works on [[pramana]] (valid cognition, [[epistemology]]), including commentaries on the writings of [[Dharmakirti]]. Only one of his works survives in the original [[Sanskrit]], the Nyāyabinduṭīkā, while other survive in Tibetan translation.<ref>Lal Mani Joshi, Studies in the Buddhistic Culture of India During the 7th and 8th Centuries A.D., page 165.</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Dharmottara (740-800)|url=http://east.uni-hd.de/buddh/ind/18/|website=Epistemology and Argumentation in South Asia and Tibet|accessdate=18 January 2016}}</ref>
